HEADWORD: Incineration
<hw>In*cin`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>incineratio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incin⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of incinerating, or the state of being incinerated;
cremation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The phenix kind,⟦br⟧
